<br><b><font color="#000001">"Im a Doctor Not a Dragon Slayer"</font></b></center><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugherad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gherad</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>4/30/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>10:52:36 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: What you get when you hit 55</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Jiva is great for small xp groups, but I've never interrupted an adjuntunt with it.  It was my understanding that they were immune to spell based interruptions.  I've use Jiva, stuns, Jyl's, all to no effect.  Perhaps you just had a tank friend bash him at the same time you casted so you thought it worked.<br>
<br>
Yes, lure of flame is great, but it is just a new flavor, not a new line.  Tears is also just a new flavor (and the usefullness of tears is very low).  Plainsight is a nice spell I use a lot, but hardly anything that aids in combat.<br>
