<P><i><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A> at: 5/3/01 9:14:44 am</FONT><br></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Sorcerer</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/3/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>12:20:46 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: What you get when you hit 55</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I like Translocate a lot, but for proper perspective, look at what other classes get at 50 and decide what was uber.  Take a look at Magicians at level 29, they get jack that level, we get evacs and group ports.  It's all relative.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uprincetoneci.showPublicProfile?language=EN>princeton eci</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Wizard</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/5/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2:48:25 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: What you get when you hit 55</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Well I guess my main complaint is that our main DD lines (draughts and lures) seem to remain basically the same throughout the whole range of 51 to 59.<br>
<br>
It's fustrating to be trudging through 54 like I am (54 makes 51 look like a piece of cake) and look to 55 and see that the big(?) upgrade? to our utility DD, Draught of Fire (3 seconds casting, 215 mana, 643 - 688 damage) is Draught of Jiva (3 seconds casting, 215 mana, 663 - 688 damage, small stun). Lure of Flame (4.5 seconds casting, 320 mana, 640 damage) is identical to Lure of Frost (4.5 seconds casting, 320 mana, 640 damage) except that it's fire based.<br>
<br>
Then I look way up to level 57 and find Draught of Flame goes way(?) up to 716 - 731 damage for the same casting time and mana? Lure of Lighting same stats?<br>
<br>
I just think that like &quot;Harvest&quot; when seems like Verant didn't scale it properly post 50, our DDs and lures are not scaled properly past 50. 50-60 is as big a distance as 1 to 49 in terms of play time. Up to 50 I have basically no complaints, but post 50 we don't scale right.<br>
<br>
Is this a whine? sigh maybe. I don't view myself as a whiner. But gosh guys: is asking the designers of the game for more equality a &quot;whine&quot; when they're making additions to other classes in the name of &quot;balance&quot;? Well, at least I posted this on the &quot;rant&quot; board.<br>
<br>
Princeton<br>
